2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20applies%20to%20anyone%20born%20after%20December%2031%2C%201970.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20which%20passed%20with%2081%20votes%20in%20favor%20and%2021%20against%2C%20marks%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20changes%20to%20the%20state%20pension%20age%20in%20Europe.%20It%20also%20signals%20a%20broader%20shift%20in%20how%20developed%20economies%20are%20preparing%20for%20aging%20populations%20and%20mounting%20fiscal%20pressures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20stems%20from%20a%202006%20welfare%20agreement%20that%20ties%20the%20pension%20age%20eligibility%20to%20life%20expectancy.%20With%20people%20living%20longer%2C%20the%20government%20argues%20that%20raising%20the%20retirement%20age%20was%20needed%20to%20keep%20the%20pension%20system%20financially%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202040%2C%20we%20will%20raise%20the%20retirement%20age%20from%2069%20to%2070%20years%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20to%20afford%20proper%20welfare%20for%20future%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20Ane%20Halsboe-J%C3%B8rgensen%2C%20Denmark's%20employment%20minister%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20following%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it%20would%20be%20the%20last%20time%20her%20party%20voted%20for%20an%20increase%20under%20the%20current%20system%2C%20citing%20the%20need%20for%20a%20fairer%20model%20that%20reflected%20differences%20in%20career%20length%20and%20job%20type.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20has%20sparked%20anger%20from%20unions%20and%20workers%20in%20physically%20demanding%20sectors%20such%20as%20construction%20and%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDenmark's%20largest%20trade%20union%2C%203F%2C%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20policy%20will%20disproportionately%20burden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-retire-still-working-retirement-age-social-security-inflation-health-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elower-income%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20said%20surveys%20had%20found%20three-quarters%20of%20their%20members%20doubted%20they%20could%20keep%20working%20into%20their%2070s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPension%20changes%20have%20become%20a%20flash%20point%20across%20Europe.%20Just%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20France%20was%20rocked%20by%20months%20of%20mass%20protests%20and%20strikes%20after%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron's%20government%20raised%20the%20retirement%20age%20from%2062%20to%2064.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20as%20demographic%20pressure%20mounts%20globally%2C%20Denmark's%20move%20may%20be%20a%20bellwether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20including%20Germany%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20have%20already%20scheduled%20retirement%20age%20increases%20to%2067%20by%202031%2C%202028%2C%20and%202028%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstill-working-past-retirement-age-never-been-burned-out-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20life%20expectancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20continuing%20to%20rise%2C%20birth%20rates%20falling%2C%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20sustainable%20ratio%20of%20workers%20to%20retirees%2C%20economists%20and%20researchers%20say%20retirement%20ages%20will%20probably%20need%20to%20be%20pushed%20back%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20report%20from%20the%20UK's%20International%20Longevity%20Centre%20projected%20that%20Britain%20would%20have%20to%20raise%20the%20retirement%20age%20to%2071%20by%202050%20to%20maintain%20the%20ratio%20of%20workers%20to%20retirees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20retirement%20age%20for%20full%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20has%20already%20been%20raised%20from%2065%20to%2067.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Republicans%20have%20proposed%20a%20further%20increase%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20the%20campaign%20trail%20in%20June%202024%20that%20he%20would%20%26quot%3Bnot%20raise%20the%20retirement%20age%20by%20one